# Feature Toggles

Remote feature toggles control features without app updates via `@ContributesRemoteFeature` interfaces returning `Toggle` objects.

## Creating Toggles

### Standalone (most common)

```kotlin
@ContributesRemoteFeature(
    scope = AppScope::class,
    featureName = "tabSwitcherAnimation",
)
interface TabSwitcherAnimationFeature {
    @Toggle.DefaultValue(DefaultFeatureValue.FALSE)
    fun self(): Toggle
}
```

Requirements: `@ContributesRemoteFeature` with `scope` + `featureName` (camelCase, matches remote config key), a `self()` method with `@Toggle.DefaultValue`, returns `Toggle`, must be an interface.

### Grouped

Add a new method to an existing `@ContributesRemoteFeature` interface (e.g., `AndroidBrowserConfigFeature`).

### API/Impl separation

Define a clean interface in the API module (no annotation). In the Impl module, create a private trigger with `boundType` pointing to the API interface:

```kotlin
@ContributesRemoteFeature(
    scope = AppScope::class,
    boundType = YourFeatureToggles::class,
    featureName = "yourFeatureName",
)
@Suppress("unused")
private interface YourFeatureTogglesTrigger
```

## Default Values

| Annotation | Use for |
|---|---|
| `DefaultFeatureValue.FALSE` | New features, gradual rollouts (most common) |
| `DefaultFeatureValue.TRUE` | Kill switches, established features needing remote disable |
| `DefaultFeatureValue.INTERNAL` | Dev/internal-only (`true` internal, `false` production) |

`@Toggle.InternalAlwaysEnabled` forces toggle ON in internal builds regardless of remote config.

## Sub-Features

Add methods to the interface for related behaviors. Always check `self()` before sub-features. Use camelCase method names (`enable*`, `show*`, `use*`).

## Using Toggles

- Inject the feature interface, call `toggle.isEnabled()`
- Always check `self()` before sub-features
- **Never cache** toggle values — call `isEnabled()` each time
- Use `toggle.enabled()` Flow for reactive observation

## Dependencies

```groovy
implementation project(':feature-toggles:feature-toggles-api')
implementation project(':anvil:anvil-annotations')
implementation project(':di')
```

## Naming

- `featureName`: camelCase, descriptive, specific, under 30 chars
- Methods: camelCase verbs — `enable*`, `show*`, `use*`
- One file per feature toggle interface, separate from implementation